Brown ground beef. Add tomato sauce, chilies, garlic, cheese, salt and pepper. Pat out each biscuit on cookie sheet and put about 2 tablespoons of beef mixture on each biscuit. Fold biscuits in half and seal the edges by crimping the dough by hand or with a fork. Brush top of empanadas with egg and bake for 15 minutes at 375 degrees F. Optional: Serve with sour cream or a mango-peach salsa on the side.